						               													<description>The original version of the game was played in Ancient Greece. One individual is blind-folded in order to catch or touch one of the others who run around.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Remoundo games, the publisher of this game, brought this traditional game on the table with the title &amp;quot;&amp;tau;&amp;upsilon;&amp;phi;&amp;lambda;&amp;#207;&amp;#140;&amp;mu;&amp;upsilon;&amp;gamma;&amp;alpha;&amp;quot; which  means &amp;quot;blind fly&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There are two different ways to play, depending on the double-sided board.&amp;#10;Side A (blue) : One player, designated as &amp;quot;It&amp;quot;, is blindfolded and the other players choose a pawn. Everybody's places their pawns on the board and they try to avoid the &amp;quot;it&amp;quot; from catching their pawn. If  &amp;quot;it&amp;quot; catches a pawn , he/she places it randomly on the board. The board indicates some sounds (animal sounds, human sounds etc) and the person who had this pawn must immitate this sound. &amp;quot;It&amp;quot; has to recognise him/her . If so, the person who recognised gets a penalty card and becomes the new &amp;quot;it&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Side B (green) : The &amp;quot;it&amp;quot; chases the other people by rolling dice. There are also 27 character cards (with 3 dinstict elements each)and everyone takes a secret caracter card trying not to reveal their character as they run to escape from &amp;quot;it&amp;quot;. If the &amp;quot;it&amp;quot; catch a player, he/she can ask them 2 more questions and if he/she find their secret character they take a penalty card and they become the new &amp;quot;it&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When a player reaches the 6 penalty cards, everybody checks their own penalty and the person with the fewest cards is the winner of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
